summary: A letter from UMB Bank's Legal Process Specialist to the Southern District of New York stating that no records were found in response to a subpoena request related to Ghislaine Maxwell. This indicates law enforcement was seeking financial records from Maxwell's accounts around the time of her arrest.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The customer for whom UMB Bank received a subpoena from the Southern District of New York, indicating law enforcement was seeking her financial records.

events.title: UMB Bank responds to SDNY subpoena
events.description: UMB Bank's Legal Process Specialist sends a letter to the Southern District of New York stating they were unable to find any records responsive to a subpoena request for Ghislaine Maxwell's accounts.

locations: 1 ST Andrew's Plaza New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: The Southern District of New York subpoenaed UMB Bank for records related to Ghislaine Maxwell on or before June 10, 2020.
UMB Bank found no records responsive to the subpoena request for Maxwell's accounts.
This document shows law enforcement was actively investigating Maxwell's financial activities around the time of her arrest in July 2020.
